                data: {},
                marks: [],
                value:
                  "The ability of a politician to clearly and concisely articulate their agenda is essential to the success of any political campaign. The candidate's political stance can be found in the platform, which defines the independent candidate’s views, objectives, and strategies about the most pressing political issues of the day. Candidates who construct their manifestos with care have a greater chance of connecting with voters and demonstrating their areas of expertise, years of experience, and leadership abilities. Additionally, it informs voters of the candidate's or party's intended priorities and platforms if elected. It is crucial to have a well-defined manifesto to win elections, gain voter trust, and determine the course of action for the campaign.",
