                data: {},
                marks: [],
                value:
                  "To succeed, candidates for political office must devise strategies that distinguish them from their opponents like transparency in government. It requires developing a unique selling proposition (USP) that distinguishes the candidate from others in the industry. A unique selling proposition (USP) distinguishes the candidate's message from others. A persuasive unique selling proposition (USP) can assist electors in forming more favourable opinions of a candidate and increasing support among that group.",
